  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NativeIdentityChangePropagator

    public class NativeIdentityChangeRolePropagatorCorrelationModel
extends AbstractNativeIdentityChangeRolePropagator
    A role propagator which searches the in-memory CorrelationModel for relevant Bundles rather than querying the database. This should be fast and should give a smaller, more exact result than a Hibernate query would.

    • Method Detail

      • getAffectedObjectIds

        protected java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> getAffectedObjectIds(SailPointContext context,
                                                                    java.util.List<NativeIdentityChangeEvent> events)
                                                             throws GeneralException
        Returns an iterator over ids of Bundles. Be aware this will be a List-backed iterator so all ids will be loaded into memory. The list can be further filtered by a filter string supplied via the "filterString" config attribute.

        Since this implementation searches the CorrelationModel rather than querying the database, the external filter string can only refer to attributes of CorrelationModel.CorrelationRole and not the whole Bundle.

        Specified by:
        getAffectedObjectIds in class AbstractNativeIdentityChangeRolePropagator
        Parameters:
        context - The SailPoint context
        events - The list of NativeIdentityChangeEvents
        Returns:
        an iterator over Bundle ids; if no ids are found an empty iterator is returned
        Throws:
        GeneralException
